g.text: For the period 1900-1960, BABO has 4.65-5.1 times more data (interquartile range).
The solid red line shows a loess smoothing curve based on 60 possibilities
(extrapolating from the Harvard dataset) per each year for the period of 1961-2019.
Based on this extrapolation (grey dots), the number of books published in Egypt by 2020 is
at least about 200 thousand, but quite likely between 400 and 450 thousand. (The solid
blue line shows the cumulative graph of Egyptian books in the Harvard Library.
